headline: Bumble Stock Tumbles as Users Depart, Issues Soft Outlook
summary: On Wednesday, shares of Bumble tumbled after the online dating service issued a weaker-than-expected first-quarter outlook and said it lost 57,000 paying customers in the fourth quarter versus the third.

headline: Bumble shares slide after weak forecast signals slow dating app turnaround
summary: (Reuters) -Bumble's shares fell 28% on Wednesday after the dating app operator forecast first-quarter revenue below market estimates, as it continues to grapple with a slowdown in the growth of paying users.  Bumble recently announced executive changes including the return of its founder Whitney Wolfe Herd as its chief executive in March.  As of last close, Bumble's valuation stood at $876.3 million compared with Tinder-parent Match Group's $8.85 billion.
